WEBVTT

00:01:20.208 --> 00:01:21.740
"There was a time

00:01:21.742 --> 00:01:23.907
"when meadow, grove, and stream,

00:01:23.909 --> 00:01:25.840
"The earth,
and every common sight,

00:01:25.842 --> 00:01:27.073
"To me did seem

00:01:27.075 --> 00:01:29.340
"Apparell'd in celestial light,

00:01:29.342 --> 00:01:32.240
"The glory and the freshness
of a dream.

00:01:32.242 --> 00:01:34.808
"It is not now
as it hath been of yore;

00:01:34.810 --> 00:01:36.741
"Turn wheresoe'er I may,

00:01:36.743 --> 00:01:38.574
"By night or day,

00:01:38.576 --> 00:01:41.808
The things which I have seen
I now can see no more."

00:02:01.011 --> 00:02:02.709
Hey.

00:02:08.311 --> 00:02:10.210
What's wrong?

00:02:10.212 --> 00:02:12.677
Nothing...

00:02:12.679 --> 00:02:14.744
I suppose.

00:02:14.746 --> 00:02:16.478
Huh.

00:02:31.413 --> 00:02:35.345
Good morning, Miss Mantel.

00:02:38.148 --> 00:02:40.480
Sit.

00:02:41.647 --> 00:02:44.814
To the front, please, Abigail.

00:02:49.482 --> 00:02:55.914
School regulations
dictate, as you well know,

00:02:55.916 --> 00:02:59.381
skirts should be
no more than two inches

00:02:59.383 --> 00:03:02.714
from the ground when kneeling.

00:03:11.684 --> 00:03:12.982
Up.

00:03:17.551 --> 00:03:22.316
And those are not regulation.

00:03:22.318 --> 00:03:25.883
Stop your clowning.

00:03:25.885 --> 00:03:30.284
It'll get you nowhere,
Abigail Mortimer.

00:03:36.552 --> 00:03:38.185
Ha ha!

00:04:03.554 --> 00:04:06.986
An egg is a cell.

00:04:06.988 --> 00:04:10.987
It has a nucleus and membrane.

00:04:16.088 --> 00:04:17.687
Oh.

00:04:17.689 --> 00:04:20.721
When the yolk matures,
the follicular sac ruptures.

00:04:20.723 --> 00:04:23.022
If any blood vessels
cross the stigma,

00:04:23.024 --> 00:04:25.388
a small drop of blood
may get on a yolk

00:04:25.390 --> 00:04:27.355
as it's released
from the follicle.

00:04:27.357 --> 00:04:30.022
It's what causes
most blood spots in eggs.

00:04:30.024 --> 00:04:32.556
Egg first or chicken,
Mr. Hopkins?

00:04:32.558 --> 00:04:36.223
The egg's still
a mystery to scientists.

00:04:36.225 --> 00:04:38.489
It's complex.

00:04:38.491 --> 00:04:41.123
It's a tiny center of life.

00:04:42.724 --> 00:04:44.924
And she's, like,
all acting like...

00:04:44.926 --> 00:04:46.490
Ha ha ha!

00:04:46.492 --> 00:04:49.191
See her, like, scurrying
through the cupboards.

00:04:49.193 --> 00:04:51.157
"I'm running late!"

00:04:51.159 --> 00:04:57.124
Ha ha ha!

00:05:14.760 --> 00:05:16.826
What's in it?

00:05:18.194 --> 00:05:21.126
I used to have hair your color.

00:05:23.194 --> 00:05:25.260
Have I told you that?

00:05:25.262 --> 00:05:27.626
No. I don't think so,
Mrs. Lamont.

00:05:30.261 --> 00:05:33.527
Oh, come on.
We've heard it millions.

00:05:51.729 --> 00:05:53.762
Thanks, Abbie.

00:05:53.764 --> 00:05:55.162
You're an angel.

00:06:26.833 --> 00:06:29.532
Just look.

00:06:33.834 --> 00:06:36.699
Imagine what it's seen.

00:06:36.701 --> 00:06:38.899
In time, this mantled oak,

00:06:38.901 --> 00:06:42.834
let's meet underneath it
the same day every year

00:06:42.836 --> 00:06:44.733
for the rest of our lives.

00:06:56.869 --> 00:07:00.601
"The moon doth with delight

00:07:00.603 --> 00:07:05.068
"Look round her when
the heavens are bare,

00:07:05.070 --> 00:07:09.036
"Waters on a starry night

00:07:09.038 --> 00:07:10.335
Are beautiful..."

00:07:11.838 --> 00:07:13.669
"and fair."

00:07:20.004 --> 00:07:24.103
"There was a time
when meadow, grove, and stream,

00:07:24.105 --> 00:07:25.903
"The earth,
and every common sight,

00:07:25.905 --> 00:07:27.337
"To me did seem

00:07:27.339 --> 00:07:29.604
"Apparell'd in celestial light,

00:07:29.606 --> 00:07:32.571
"The glory and the freshness
of a dream.

00:07:32.573 --> 00:07:35.571
"It is not now
as it hath been of yore;

00:07:35.573 --> 00:07:37.371
"Turn wheresoe'er I may,

00:07:37.373 --> 00:07:39.371
"By night or day,

00:07:39.373 --> 00:07:42.971
The things which I have seen
I now can see no more."

00:07:54.740 --> 00:07:57.773
"The Rainbow comes and goes,

00:07:57.775 --> 00:07:59.739
"And lovely is the Rose,

00:07:59.741 --> 00:08:01.240
"The Moon doth with delight

00:08:01.242 --> 00:08:04.273
"Look round her
when the heavens are bare,

00:08:04.275 --> 00:08:06.273
"Waters on a starry night

00:08:06.275 --> 00:08:08.340
Are beautiful and fair."

00:08:08.342 --> 00:08:12.074
Try not to be quite so emphatic.

00:08:17.576 --> 00:08:22.608
"The sunshine
is a glorious birth;

00:08:22.610 --> 00:08:27.576
"But yet I know, where'er I go,

00:08:27.578 --> 00:08:30.075
That there hath past
a glory from the earth."

00:08:33.511 --> 00:08:35.342
That will do.

00:10:21.186 --> 00:10:25.018
When that's gone all the way in,

00:10:25.020 --> 00:10:27.185
slide the other tube up, too,

00:10:27.187 --> 00:10:29.619
then pull them both out.

00:10:29.621 --> 00:10:31.319
Any questions?

00:10:37.554 --> 00:10:41.086
As you know, I'm a virgin.

00:10:41.088 --> 00:10:42.553
So?

00:10:42.555 --> 00:10:45.054
Virgins can use them.

00:10:45.056 --> 00:10:46.787
Anyway,

00:10:46.789 --> 00:10:48.954
let's establish your
status, shall we?

00:10:48.956 --> 00:10:50.120
Oh, Lamb...

00:10:50.122 --> 00:10:53.020
You lost it, Abbie, didn't you?

00:10:53.022 --> 00:10:56.855
In a car.
What can I say?

00:10:56.857 --> 00:10:59.088
I don't get it.

00:11:02.423 --> 00:11:05.822
Close your eyes.
Kiss your lips.

00:11:11.390 --> 00:11:18.089
Ha ha ha!

00:11:18.091 --> 00:11:20.323
It takes you somewhere else.

00:11:24.859 --> 00:11:25.923
Abbie?

00:11:43.192 --> 00:11:45.992
That's why you're upset.

00:11:47.593 --> 00:11:50.392
But...

00:11:50.394 --> 00:11:53.359
I can't be.

00:11:53.361 --> 00:11:54.926
He pulled out early,

00:11:54.928 --> 00:11:57.826
said it was a really
Catholic thing to do.

00:11:59.594 --> 00:12:03.393
Yeah. We know.
The bell's rung.

00:12:03.395 --> 00:12:06.427
Sorry.
They're not my rules.

00:12:13.028 --> 00:12:15.761
Don't tell anyone,

00:12:15.763 --> 00:12:18.695
but we think I'm pregnant.

00:12:20.030 --> 00:12:24.429
Ha ha ha!

00:12:45.265 --> 00:12:47.697
Ha ha ha!

00:12:50.532 --> 00:12:53.264
Crowd goes wild.
Ha ha ha!

00:12:55.198 --> 00:13:00.398
So... not seen you
in a while, Abbie.

00:13:00.400 --> 00:13:04.866
Been busy, Kenneth Nevercan.

00:13:08.766 --> 00:13:10.233
Looks that way.

00:13:10.235 --> 00:13:12.132
Ha ha ha!

00:13:12.134 --> 00:13:14.299
It's your turn to go
to the launderette.

00:13:14.301 --> 00:13:17.299
Yeah, yeah, Crazy Face.

00:13:17.301 --> 00:13:19.466
Don't get your
knickers in a twist.

00:13:19.468 --> 00:13:20.466
Come on.

00:13:20.468 --> 00:13:21.466
Abbie...
Hmm?

00:13:21.468 --> 00:13:22.466
Do you mind just grabbing

00:13:22.468 --> 00:13:23.467
a couple of the things

00:13:23.469 --> 00:13:25.100
out of the laundry basket?

00:13:25.102 --> 00:13:29.467
Stop.
OK.

00:13:33.735 --> 00:13:37.034
I was an egg.

00:13:37.036 --> 00:13:40.635
Now I've made an egg.

00:13:40.637 --> 00:13:44.869
Actually, we're already
born with all our eggs.

00:13:44.871 --> 00:13:47.969
I feel so crummy.

00:13:47.971 --> 00:13:50.636
Pregnancy's no good for you.

00:13:50.638 --> 00:13:54.970
Look at our mothers.
Ha ha!

00:13:54.972 --> 00:13:57.336
You've always had it in
for your mum, haven't you?

00:13:58.937 --> 00:14:01.103
Me?

00:14:01.105 --> 00:14:04.370
Morty, she's had it in for me

00:14:04.372 --> 00:14:06.737
since the day I was conceived.

00:14:20.806 --> 00:14:24.305
Gin and a knitting needle.

00:14:24.307 --> 00:14:25.771
Yeah.

00:14:25.773 --> 00:14:27.839
Mm...

00:14:33.440 --> 00:14:37.373
I'm definitely bigger.
They're killing me.

00:14:41.741 --> 00:14:44.074
Oh...

00:14:44.076 --> 00:14:45.907
You've changed.
Ha!

00:14:45.909 --> 00:14:48.341
Did we extend the invitation?

00:14:57.409 --> 00:14:59.608
Oh, loosen up, Crazy Face.

00:14:59.610 --> 00:15:01.575
I don't want to be loose.

00:15:05.409 --> 00:15:07.675
Oh, nice.

00:15:12.643 --> 00:15:14.409
"Everything that lives

00:15:14.411 --> 00:15:16.109
"serves the purposes
of the earth.

00:15:16.111 --> 00:15:18.576
Everything that dies
serves the moon."

00:15:18.578 --> 00:15:21.877
Huh?

00:15:21.879 --> 00:15:23.943
You know I'm pregnant.
Ugh!

00:15:23.945 --> 00:15:25.244
She's telling everyone.

00:15:25.246 --> 00:15:27.744
You're in trouble?
Kenneth!

00:15:27.746 --> 00:15:30.410
Let's do some magik

00:15:30.412 --> 00:15:33.944
