Miss Mantel, honestly.

00:25:50.531 --> 00:25:53.297
I feel so awful.

00:25:53.299 --> 00:25:57.630
Crying out loud, oh...

00:25:57.632 --> 00:26:01.497
Oh, I've better things to do
with my time than this.

00:26:01.499 --> 00:26:03.664
Out. Out.

00:26:33.367 --> 00:26:35.767
Say something, please.

00:26:35.769 --> 00:26:38.167
We'll always be,
whatever happens.

00:26:38.168 --> 00:26:39.833
What do you want me to say?

00:26:39.835 --> 00:26:41.000
I'm sure you have
something in mind.

00:26:41.002 --> 00:26:42.134
You always seem to these days.

00:26:42.136 --> 00:26:43.467
You even sided with my mother.

00:26:43.469 --> 00:26:45.367
Oh, don't be like that.

00:26:45.369 --> 00:26:47.267
Come on.
I know she's awful.

00:26:47.269 --> 00:26:49.267
Please, I'm really
not up for a fight.

00:26:49.269 --> 00:26:53.201
Admit it.
You think we're over.

00:26:53.203 --> 00:26:55.801
Say it.

00:26:55.803 --> 00:26:58.468
You're getting it up,
and I'm not right anymore.

00:26:58.470 --> 00:27:00.702
I'm feeling very...

00:27:00.704 --> 00:27:02.702
You and your feelings.

00:27:02.704 --> 00:27:05.036
Millions of women
have had babies, Abbie.

00:27:05.038 --> 00:27:09.803
It's nothing special.
It's life and life only.

00:27:12.004 --> 00:27:14.137
Abbie?

00:27:21.104 --> 00:27:22.437
Abbie?

00:27:24.204 --> 00:27:26.104
Abbie?

00:27:26.106 --> 00:27:29.138
Abbie, it's Lamb.

00:27:29.140 --> 00:27:31.471
It's Lydia.
Come on, Abbie.

00:27:31.473 --> 00:27:34.438
Help! Please! Someone!

00:27:34.440 --> 00:27:36.038
Come on.
Come on, Abbie.

00:27:36.040 --> 00:27:37.872
Come on, Abbie.
Don't be silly.

00:27:37.874 --> 00:27:39.805
Sit up.
Come on, Abbie.

00:27:39.807 --> 00:27:41.505
Someone's coming.
It's gonna be fine.

00:27:41.507 --> 00:27:42.872
What...
What... What...

00:27:42.874 --> 00:27:44.639
Miss Mantel, I think
she's losing the baby.

00:27:44.641 --> 00:27:48.372
Well, let her get some air.

00:27:48.374 --> 00:27:52.606
Abigail? Abigail.
Get an ambulance!

00:27:58.442 --> 00:28:01.340
Abi... gail...

00:28:09.777 --> 00:28:10.841
Uh...

00:29:27.883 --> 00:29:33.148
Abbie!

00:29:36.483 --> 00:29:38.215
Abbie!

00:29:56.951 --> 00:29:58.584
Uh...

00:29:59.518 --> 00:30:02.817
Abbie's dead.

00:30:02.819 --> 00:30:05.684
Uh...

00:30:05.686 --> 00:30:07.084
Yeah.

00:30:09.018 --> 00:30:11.318
It's true.

00:30:14.186 --> 00:30:16.585
She's dead.

00:30:28.520 --> 00:30:32.386
It wasn't something bad.

00:30:32.388 --> 00:30:34.153
Uh, she's dead.

00:30:34.155 --> 00:30:35.553
Well, wasn't...

00:30:35.555 --> 00:30:37.620
What?
Drugs.

00:30:39.821 --> 00:30:42.654
It was natural.

00:30:42.656 --> 00:30:45.754
"Natural."
Abbie's young.

00:30:48.889 --> 00:30:50.955
Her poor mother.

00:31:12.691 --> 00:31:14.456
The race had been run and won.

00:31:14.458 --> 00:31:18.157
A look at the arguments
by Julian Pedwell.

00:31:18.159 --> 00:31:20.490
To most of us, man's
breathtaking adventure

00:31:20.492 --> 00:31:21.724
in space looked...

00:31:34.025 --> 00:31:37.458
We are grieved
and shocked to announce

00:31:37.460 --> 00:31:41.725
the death of Abigail Mortimer.

00:31:41.727 --> 00:31:46.960
Abigail... Abbie was a girl
of... of rare charm,

00:31:46.962 --> 00:31:52.393
a most lively,
talented, and popular pupil

00:31:52.395 --> 00:31:55.694
who had a promising future
ahead of her.

00:31:57.394 --> 00:31:59.493
Teachers have praised
her performance

00:31:59.495 --> 00:32:02.027
as a committed pupil

00:32:02.029 --> 00:32:04.361
who was energetic...

00:32:07.529 --> 00:32:09.595
and dependable.

00:32:12.329 --> 00:32:16.028
Her passing is a true loss

00:32:16.030 --> 00:32:18.195
to us all.

00:32:23.030 --> 00:32:26.229
She will be remembered
as a loyal friend

00:32:26.231 --> 00:32:29.129
who enjoyed art
and reading poetry

00:32:29.131 --> 00:32:34.496
and as the founder of the
alternative school orchestra.

00:32:34.498 --> 00:32:37.230
Abbie's life was full and happy,

00:32:37.232 --> 00:32:41.397
and we shall remember her
with respect and affection.

00:32:41.399 --> 00:32:45.364
As a memorial,
it has been decided to establish

00:32:45.366 --> 00:32:50.031
the Abigail Mortimer
Fifth Form Poetry Prize.

00:32:50.033 --> 00:32:53.231
Miss Fanshawe
will now lead assembly

00:32:53.233 --> 00:32:56.098
in nondenominational prayer.

00:33:02.001 --> 00:33:07.533
Let us take a minute
to remember Abigail in silence.

00:33:28.202 --> 00:33:31.234
You were such
a friend to us all,

00:33:31.236 --> 00:33:33.335
For Abbie Mortimer,

00:33:33.337 --> 00:33:36.235
"The good die first"...
Wordsworth.

00:33:36.237 --> 00:33:38.902
She liked him.

00:33:38.904 --> 00:33:43.502
"There hath past away
a glory from this earth."

00:33:43.504 --> 00:33:46.369
She was beautiful.

00:33:46.371 --> 00:33:52.403
You're up there with the angels.

00:33:52.405 --> 00:33:54.036
She would've made a great mum.

00:34:41.008 --> 00:34:43.574
Close your eyes.

00:34:43.576 --> 00:34:45.374
Pucker your lips.

00:34:45.376 --> 00:34:47.175
Do it.

00:35:06.677 --> 00:35:09.142
Takes you somewhere else.

00:36:36.851 --> 00:36:39.117
I'm late, Miss Mantel.

00:38:11.492 --> 00:38:15.559
"The glory
and the freshness of a dream.

00:38:15.561 --> 00:38:18.225
"It is not now
as it hath been of yore;

00:38:18.227 --> 00:38:20.092
"Turn wheresoe'er I may,

00:38:20.094 --> 00:38:22.258
"By night or day,

00:38:22.260 --> 00:38:24.326
The things which I have seen
I now can see no more."

00:38:24.328 --> 00:38:27.193
Abbie?

00:38:27.195 --> 00:38:31.126
Oh. It's you.

00:38:32.361 --> 00:38:34.393
You fainted.

00:38:40.229 --> 00:38:41.861
Don't.

00:38:43.328 --> 00:38:46.161
I can't remember much...

00:38:53.863 --> 00:38:56.996
but now

00:38:56.998 --> 00:38:59.695
I've never felt so bad.

00:38:59.697 --> 00:39:01.695
Tell me about it, Lamb.

00:39:01.697 --> 00:39:05.029
I'm feeling rotten.
Didn't want to say.

00:39:23.398 --> 00:39:30.264
It was this feeling.

00:39:33.699 --> 00:39:38.232
Yeah.

00:39:38.234 --> 00:39:42.899
I don't remember
anything before or after,

00:39:42.901 --> 00:39:45.733
just this spacey...

00:39:50.601 --> 00:39:53.734
It's showing us that
there is enough energy

00:39:53.736 --> 00:39:57.734
in a slice of cake
to walk a mile.

00:39:57.736 --> 00:40:01.101
It also helps explain
the combustion engine.

00:40:01.103 --> 00:40:02.668
And at the end of it all,

00:40:02.670 --> 00:40:06.167
there's a little
purified argon gas produced.

00:40:06.169 --> 00:40:09.501
The gas holds a few
radioactive atoms

00:40:09.503 --> 00:40:11.568
containing neutrinos.

00:40:11.570 --> 00:40:15.102
Later, the radioactivity will be
measured in these laboratories.

00:40:15.104 --> 00:40:17.968
Already they've given
one important answer to us all.

00:40:28.037 --> 00:40:32.870
"Let's meet under it
the same day every year

00:40:32.872 --> 00:40:36.237
for the rest of our lives."

00:40:48.839 --> 00:40:52.572
What was it like with her?

00:40:54.272 --> 00:40:56.338
She was something else...

00:40:59.407 --> 00:41:01.139
like...

00:41:03.674 --> 00:41:05.840
a warrior queen.

00:41:51.844 --> 00:41:53.910
How's my future?

00:42:14.246 --> 00:42:17.846
Can someone go to the shop?

00:42:20.680 --> 00:42:22.246
I'm terrified.

00:42:22.248 --> 00:42:25.346
I am terrified by his arms,
by his nuclear destruction.

00:42:25.348 --> 00:42:29.213
I think this is, perhaps,
a pathetic sign...

00:42:30.781 --> 00:42:33.047
What if we said
we're never gonna go

00:42:33.049 --> 00:42:35.747
to the shops for you ever again?

00:42:35.749 --> 00:42:39.848
I mean, you'd have to face
the real world then, hmm?

00:42:39.850 --> 00:42:43.247
When was the last time
you went outside, Mother?

00:42:43.249 --> 00:42:46.981
What are you so afraid of?

00:42:51.182 --> 00:42:53.815
Come on, please, please.

00:43:08.450 --> 00:43:11.150
Titch, time, please.

00:43:14.851 --> 00:43:18.851
I guess I forgot to wind it.

00:43:18.853 --> 00:43:21.284
Who else had the time?

00:43:21.286 --> 00:43:23.817
It's not working.

00:43:25.085 --> 00:43:30.251
Susan.
It stopped.

00:43:30.253 --> 00:43:33.885
It's a coincidence.

00:43:36.620 --> 00:43:39.185
Susan, fetch some water.

00:44:19.623 --> 00:44:22.023
Oh...

00:44:25.790 --> 00:44:27.590
Oh...

00:44:40.025 --> 00:44:42.491
Gwen, would you read?

00:44:45.892 --> 00:44:49.125
"So he, trembling
and astonished, said,

00:44:49.127 --> 00:44:52.091
"Lord, what do you
want me to do?"

00:44:52.093 --> 00:44:53.592
and the Lord said to him..."

00:44:58.127 --> 00:45:00.526
Gwen?

00:45:11.095 --> 00:45:12.860
Gwen?

00:45:32.596 --> 00:45:36.795
It's just a few neurotic types.

00:45:36.797 --> 00:45:38.429
Relax.

00:45:38.431 --> 00:45:40.029
You think the medical officer
should be brought in?

00:45:40.031 --> 00:45:41.262
We'd be the laughingstock.

00:45:41.264 --> 00:45:43.030
A few girls trying it on,

00:45:43.032 --> 00:45:45.130
making a display of themselves.

00:45:45.132 --> 00:45:47.130
We used to put wet
blotting paper in our shoes.

00:45:47.132 --> 00:45:49.463
Why?
Ha ha ha!

00:45:49.465 --> 00:45:51.030
It draws the blood
from one's head

00:45:51.032 --> 00:45:52.697
and can cause a faint, you see?

00:45:52.699 --> 00:45:54.730
Ha! They all
seem to have

00:45:54.732 --> 00:45:57.730
their mind elsewhere these days.

00:45:57.732 --> 00:45:59.930
Oh...

00:46:36.268 --> 00:46:38.067
Mm.

00:46:41.703 --> 00:46:45.201
Ooh, sickles...

00:46:45.203 --> 00:46:48.268
and pickles.

00:46:49.302 --> 00:46:51.735
The sick chicks.

00:46:55.636 --> 00:47:01.202
Are you sure you're fit
to go to school, Susan.

00:47:10.904 --> 00:47:13.936
Right. Let's go.

00:47:15.238 --> 00:47:17.737
We don't want to be late.

00:47:21.305 --> 00:47:26.071
And just look at the result
of not being educated.

00:48:06.243 --> 00:48:08.508
Settle down.
Miss Charron has merely fainted.

00:48:11.909 --> 00:48:14.375
Return to your seat, Lydia.

00:48:22.110 --> 00:48:24.976
Please continue, Miss Fanshawe.

00:48:32.779 --> 00:48:36.144
I feel pitiful.

00:48:36.146 --> 00:48:40.344
I could do a spell.

00:48:42.645 --> 00:48:45.778
As you know, I don't
believe in magic.

00:48:45.780 --> 00:48:47.412
I'm a rationalist.

00:48:47.414 --> 00:48:52.112
Oh, a rationalist.
I'm not so sure.

00:48:52.113 --> 00:48:54.912
I know my mind.

00:48:54.914 --> 00:48:58.779
What's it all about,
then, Crazy Face?

00:48:58.781 --> 00:49:01.613
It's not about anything.

00:49:05.380 --> 00:49:07.746
You see this?

00:49:07.748 --> 00:49:10.047
That one runs through the heath

00:49:10.049 --> 00:49:12.080
and under your school.

00:49:13.114 --> 00:49:18.547
Ley lines have this energy...

00:49:18.549 --> 00:49:20.881
sacred, sublime.

00:51:57.762 --> 00:51:59.461
Ohh...

00:52:04.563 --> 00:52:06.262
Open the windows.

00:53:08.301 --> 00:53:11.567
What's happening, Lydia?

00:53:22.436 --> 00:53:25.768
She...
She was so...

00:53:25.770 --> 00:53:28.468
I know. I know.

00:53:36.670 --> 00:53:38.536
Lydia...

00:53:40.737 --> 00:53:43.103
I do know what's happening.

00:53:59.138 --> 00:54:01.271
Miss Charron fainted.

00:54:01.273 --> 00:54:03.504
It's not just us.

00:54:03.506 --> 00:54:05.738
How come you're not ill, Titch?

00:54:05.740 --> 00:54:07.172
I don't know.

00:54:07.174 --> 00:54:11.472
For whatever reasons,
Titch, you're immune.

00:54:13.740 --> 00:54:16.439
Titch doesn't believe us.

00:54:16.441 --> 00:54:17.906
I mean, why hasn't

00:54:17.908 --> 00:54:19.173
Miss Alvaro got the doctors in?

00:54:19.175 --> 00:54:21.139
Oh, such a woman of the world.

00:54:21.141 --> 00:54:23.940
She is.

00:54:23.942 --> 00:54:27.807
She's the one thinking
you're making it up.

00:54:29.308 --> 00:54:31.174
I don't like to criticize,

00:54:31.176 --> 00:54:34.674
but the handling of this
has not been great, has it?

00:54:34.676 --> 00:54:37.607
Some people just want to bury
their heads in the sand.

00:54:50.110 --> 00:54:54.176
It's been
a difficult time, I know.

00:54:54.178 --> 00:54:58.076
Don't throw your potential away.

00:54:58.078 --> 00:55:00.843
Do you need some time
off school, Lydia?

00:55:00.845 --> 00:55:04.277
No. No.

00:55:04.279 --> 00:55:07.343
There's been some
concern expressed.

00:55:07.345 --> 00:55:09.810
You're quite an influence
on the others

00:55:09.812 --> 00:55:11.177
with what you are doing.

00:55:11.179 --> 00:55:13.310
I'm not doing anything.

00:55:16.112 --> 00:55:19.144
I'd like your parents...

00:55:19.146 --> 00:55:22.812
your mother to come and see me.

00:55:47.815 --> 00:55:49.613
There you go.

00:55:51.748 --> 00:55:54.014
Thanks.
Bye.

00:55:54.016 --> 00:55:55.614
Bye.

00:55:55.616 --> 00:55:57.947
Bye.
Bye.

00:55:57.949 --> 00:56:03.347
Don't you know beehives
are completely outmoded, Mother?

00:56:03.349 --> 00:56:05.681
Miss Alvaro
would like to see you.

00:56:05.683 --> 00:56:09.315
You know, I reckon
it's in my official records

00:56:09.317 --> 00:56:12.682
that my father ran off.

00:56:12.684 --> 00:56:16.849
Should I say "driven off"?

00:56:16.851 --> 00:56:19.782
Should I make you
an appointment to go in?

00:56:21.351 --> 00:56:24.083
Hmm?

00:56:24.085 --> 00:56:26.150
Monday?

00:56:27.984 --> 00:56:29.717
Tuesday?

00:56:30.951 --> 00:56:34.584
Any day of the week?

00:57:02.821 --> 00:57:05.454
What have you done?

00:57:06.421 --> 00:57:08.153
Nothing.

00:57:15.855 --> 00:57:19.088
"The late Carl Jung
wrote of changes

00:57:19.090 --> 00:57:21.954
"in the constellation
of psychic dominance

00:57:21.956 --> 00:57:24.621
"which bring about
long-lasting transformations

00:57:24.623 --> 00:57:27.155
"of the collective psyche.

00:57:27.157 --> 00:57:29.255
Old secrets
rise to the surface..."

00:57:29.257 --> 00:57:30.688
Pbbt!

00:57:32.990 --> 00:57:34.989
Sorry.

00:57:34.991 --> 00:57:37.689
I don't know why I'm
shaking like this.

00:57:37.691 --> 00:57:38.989
Why are you dancing?

00:57:38.991 --> 00:57:40.756
Ha ha ha!
Ha ha ha!

00:57:40.758 --> 00:57:42.290
You're laughing at me.

00:57:42.292 --> 00:57:43.623
Well, I'm laughing at me, too,

00:57:43.625 --> 00:57:45.989
but it's not funny, Kenneth.

00:58:15.127 --> 00:58:18.593
"to the surface and dissolve

00:58:18.595 --> 00:58:21.927
"into the consciousness
of the human race

00:58:21.929 --> 00:58:26.127
to fertilize the seed
of evolutionary growth."

00:59:14.598 --> 00:59:17.764
The fullness of your bliss,

00:59:17.766 --> 00:59:20.164
I feel it.

00:59:20.166 --> 00:59:21.598
I feel it all.

00:59:21.600 --> 00:59:23.665
Crazy witches!
Ha ha!

00:59:35.533 --> 00:59:37.499
Don't look at me.

00:59:40.000 --> 00:59:41.933
Stand.

00:59:45.101 --> 00:59:49.633
You are not to fraternize
with any of these girls.

00:59:50.801 --> 00:59:54.167
But, Miss Mantel...
No buts.

00:59:54.169 --> 00:59:56.034
We'd like you to observe silence

00:59:56.036 --> 00:59:58.201
in the corridors and
the communal areas.

00:59:58.203 --> 00:59:59.935
You will not attend assemblies,

00:59:59.937 --> 01:00:03.268
and you'll be
taking games alone.

01:00:05.870 --> 01:00:08.102
On now.

01:00:10.703 --> 01:00:13.302
They stink.

01:01:36.610 --> 01:01:40.609
May I have absolute silence?

01:01:40.611 --> 01:01:42.577
I want to hear a pin drop.

01:02:00.812 --> 01:02:03.878
We're very fortunate
to have Mrs. Maud Leese

01:02:03.880 --> 01:02:06.845
from the Stockshire
Women's Circle joining us today

01:02:06.847 --> 01:02:11.245
to give a talk entitled
"Accidents in the Home."

01:02:15.613 --> 01:02:17.313
Good morning.

01:02:17.315 --> 01:02:20.146
I wonder how many girls
are aware of the work

01:02:20.148 --> 01:02:22.346
of the Women's Circle.

01:02:24.014 --> 01:02:25.713
I see.

01:02:25.715 --> 01:02:27.546
Well, I have brought leaflets

01:02:27.548 --> 01:02:29.847
that can be given out
afterwards.

01:02:29.849 --> 01:02:33.481
As Miss Alvaro has informed you,
I'm here today to talk

01:02:33.483 --> 01:02:36.781
about accidents in the home.

01:02:36.783 --> 01:02:40.848
Unfortunately, your home
is the place where...

01:02:40.850 --> 01:02:42.315
I'm sorry.

01:02:42.317 --> 01:02:44.982
accidents are most
likely to occur.

01:02:44.984 --> 01:02:46.215
Girls.

01:02:46.217 --> 01:02:47.548
They are frequently
either burns or...

01:02:47.550 --> 01:02:49.849
Girls. For crying
out loud.

01:03:07.118 --> 01:03:08.784
I'm so sorry.

01:03:18.552 --> 01:03:20.084
Oh...

01:05:53.898 --> 01:05:55.831
"Everything that lives

01:05:55.833 --> 01:05:57.531
"serves the purposes
of the earth.

01:05:57.533 --> 01:06:00.165
"Everything that dies
serves the moon.

01:06:00.167 --> 01:06:02.298
"Everything that lives serves
the purposes of the earth.

01:06:02.300 --> 01:06:04.565
Everything that dies..."

01:06:04.567 --> 01:06:06.298
Now, girls...

01:06:06.300 --> 01:06:09.298
"Everything that dies
serves to moon."

01:06:09.300 --> 01:06:11.032
Now today
I'm going to talk to you

01:06:11.034 --> 01:06:12.665
about the devil.

01:06:12.667 --> 01:06:15.966
The devil can enter you
in many ways.

01:06:15.968 --> 01:06:18.533
So please cross you legs.

01:06:34.169 --> 01:06:37.502
I feel so crummy.

01:06:37.504 --> 01:06:39.034
"Accidents in the..."

01:06:39.036 --> 01:06:41.635
Accidents in the Home."

01:06:44.003 --> 01:06:46.069
I have brought leaflets

01:06:46.071 --> 01:06:47.368
which can be given out.

01:06:47.370 --> 01:06:49.002
Shows the test results.

01:07:12.505 --> 01:07:15.471
I haven't got a decent coat.

01:07:15.473 --> 01:07:18.338
Go on, mum.

01:07:18.340 --> 01:07:21.038
Do it for me,

01:07:21.040 --> 01:07:24.905
for me.

01:07:24.907 --> 01:07:28.806
Take anything she might need.

01:07:28.808 --> 01:07:32.139
Good idea.

01:07:35.007 --> 01:07:38.240
Why can't you care?

01:07:38.242 --> 01:07:41.874
That what you were doing?

01:07:41.876 --> 01:07:43.640
Mm...

01:08:11.543 --> 01:08:13.809
The school has been shut down.

01:08:13.811 --> 01:08:15.842
Shh!

01:08:15.844 --> 01:08:17.710
Kenneth Nevercan.

01:08:17.712 --> 01:08:21.343
You're the brother.
Yep.

01:08:25.478 --> 01:08:28.210
You must believe
something's wrong now.

01:08:28.212 --> 01:08:30.911
I suppose all this
can't be from nothing.

01:08:30.913 --> 01:08:33.145
It's them and us, Titch.

01:08:36.179 --> 01:08:39.044
Don't look at me like that.

01:08:39.046 --> 01:08:41.345
You make me feel
I'm making this up.

01:08:41.347 --> 01:08:43.545
If it's how you feel,

01:08:43.547 --> 01:08:45.311
it's how you feel.

01:08:45.313 --> 01:08:46.745
Right.

01:08:46.747 --> 01:08:48.179
I don't know.

01:08:48.181 --> 01:08:49.479
It's like Ouspensky said...

01:08:49.481 --> 01:08:51.579
"To be free,
one must be conscious."

01:08:51.581 --> 01:08:55.212
Seems simple,
but it's not simple.

01:08:55.214 --> 01:08:58.013
It's all about...

01:08:59.414 --> 01:09:00.880
perception.

01:09:04.981 --> 01:09:08.847
Sometimes I wonder who you see

01:09:08.849 --> 01:09:11.148
when you look at me.

01:09:11.150 --> 01:09:14.348
I see my friend Lydia,

01:09:14.350 --> 01:09:19.381
and I see a powerful
personality.

01:09:19.383 --> 01:09:20.948
"Powerful."

01:09:24.316 --> 01:09:26.582
Nobody knows who I am anymore...

01:09:26.584 --> 01:09:28.749
Yeah?
Yeah.

01:09:28.751 --> 01:09:30.415
Yeah.

01:09:30.417 --> 01:09:33.216
what I'm really like...

01:09:36.151 --> 01:09:38.283
what I think about doing.

01:09:40.251 --> 01:09:42.250
I wanted you to know

01:09:42.252 --> 01:09:43.850
I've been discharged,

01:09:43.852 --> 01:09:45.483
most of the other girls, too.

01:09:45.485 --> 01:09:46.850
They didn't find anything wrong?

01:09:46.852 --> 01:09:49.217
Just...

01:09:49.219 --> 01:09:51.417
All my tests were clear.

01:09:51.419 --> 01:09:54.985
That's wonderful.
Hmm.

01:09:54.987 --> 01:09:56.885
Oh.

01:10:15.821 --> 01:10:19.653
Poor Abigail Mortimer.

01:10:19.655 --> 01:10:22.553
She thought she knew it all,

01:10:22.555 --> 01:10:24.820
naive, little thing.

01:10:24.822 --> 01:10:28.888
Abbie and Lydia, so very close.

01:10:28.890 --> 01:10:31.888
Those skirts.

01:10:34.890 --> 01:10:39.188
Lydia...

01:10:39.190 --> 01:10:42.421
Unhinged.

01:10:42.423 --> 01:10:44.588
She'll move on.

01:10:44.590 --> 01:10:46.322
The young always do.

01:10:51.390 --> 01:10:55.090
I'm sorry we have to let you go.

01:10:55.092 --> 01:10:57.689
It's OK.
It's all right.

01:10:57.691 --> 01:11:00.056
I...

01:11:00.058 --> 01:11:03.690
I was getting a little...

01:11:03.692 --> 01:11:07.290
Anyway, I have my heart.

01:11:09.558 --> 01:11:12.291
Are you going to have it?

01:11:14.726 --> 01:11:19.224
I didn't think you'd be
so understanding, Miss Mantel.

01:11:19.226 --> 01:11:21.225
It's not as if I'm married.

01:11:21.227 --> 01:11:23.825
Neither was I.

01:11:23.827 --> 01:11:25.225
You mean...

01:11:25.227 --> 01:11:28.592
Contrary to popular belief,

01:11:28.594 --> 01:11:30.893
I was never a nun.

01:11:30.895 --> 01:11:34.526
No. I was going to say,
you had a child?

01:11:38.594 --> 01:11:40.794
Ohh...

01:11:59.429 --> 01:12:01.495
Let's see, Susan.

01:12:01.497 --> 01:12:03.695
Susie.

01:12:03.697 --> 01:12:05.996
Is there any friend
in particular

01:12:05.998 --> 01:12:09.662
you especially
look up to, admire?

01:12:12.230 --> 01:12:15.229
So who was the first
person in your age group

01:12:15.231 --> 01:12:17.730
to show symptoms?

01:12:21.998 --> 01:12:25.631
If you don't want to
talk about it, just say.

01:12:29.165 --> 01:12:31.864
Any history of illness
in the family?

01:12:31.866 --> 01:12:34.564
My cousin.
She has fits.

01:12:34.566 --> 01:12:36.664
Have you witnessed a seizure?

01:12:38.166 --> 01:12:41.665
When you first noticed
your symptoms,

01:12:41.667 --> 01:12:43.832
had anything happened...

01:12:43.834 --> 01:12:48.366
exams, an illness
around you, a death?

01:12:50.200 --> 01:12:52.099
If I were a fly on the wall

01:12:52.101 --> 01:12:53.699
in your house,

01:12:53.701 --> 01:12:56.366
what would I see, Janet?

01:12:56.368 --> 01:13:01.033
Just, like, a normal family,

01:13:01.035 --> 01:13:03.734
normal like normal.

01:13:03.736 --> 01:13:07.534
Your teachers,

01:13:07.536 --> 01:13:09.433
what are they like?

01:13:09.435 --> 01:13:13.268
Well, Miss Alvaro,

01:13:13.270 --> 01:13:16.067
she wouldn't care
if we were all dead,

01:13:16.069 --> 01:13:19.501
and Miss Mantel,

01:13:19.503 --> 01:13:22.202
she's a malicious prude.

01:13:22.204 --> 01:13:24.002
I like M...

01:13:25.936 --> 01:13:27.235
Miss Charron.

01:13:27.237 --> 01:13:29.235
She's been sick, too.

01:13:29.237 --> 01:13:32.103
She's close in age to you?

01:13:32.105 --> 01:13:34.903
That's important, isn't it?

01:13:34.905 --> 01:13:36.403
I think so, too.

01:13:36.405 --> 01:13:39.503
Have you had sexual intercourse?

01:13:39.505 --> 01:13:42.436
Yeah.

01:13:42.438 --> 01:13:45.204
No.

01:13:45.206 --> 01:13:47.437
I can't really remember.

01:13:47.439 --> 01:13:50.037
Your mother?
Well is she?

01:13:50.039 --> 01:13:52.337
I haven't caught
anything off her,

01:13:52.339 --> 01:13:54.771
if that's what you mean.

01:13:54.773 --> 01:13:56.571
Do you like the
attention you get

01:13:56.573 --> 01:13:59.704
from your mother when you faint?

01:13:59.706 --> 01:14:02.872
I hate it if she
gets concerned about me.

01:14:02.874 --> 01:14:04.238
Have you had your first

01:14:04.240 --> 01:14:06.006
sexual experience, Lydia?

01:14:06.008 --> 01:14:07.906
I don't do things like that.

01:14:07.908 --> 01:14:10.439
Could you expand?

01:14:10.441 --> 01:14:12.839
I don't put dates on things.

01:14:12.841 --> 01:14:18.107
You know, I read

01:14:18.109 --> 01:14:20.873
that one person is
really like 3 people...

01:14:20.875 --> 01:14:22.673
the person you think you are,

01:14:22.675 --> 01:14:24.574
the person other people see,

01:14:24.576 --> 01:14:26.340
and the person you really are.

01:14:26.342 --> 01:14:28.340
You're a bright
girl, aren't you?

01:14:28.342 --> 01:14:29.874
Don't patronize me.

01:14:29.876 --> 01:14:31.374
Is that what
you think I'm doing?

01:14:31.376 --> 01:14:34.208
I don't know what you're
doing, if anything.

01:14:34.210 --> 01:14:36.408
I'm...

01:14:36.410 --> 01:14:39.375
I'm not...

01:14:43.210 --> 01:14:45.675
mad.

01:14:45.677 --> 01:14:47.576
I'm not.

01:14:47.578 --> 01:14:50.209
Your father?

01:14:50.211 --> 01:14:52.543
I don't know him.

01:14:52.545 --> 01:14:54.242
She drove him away.

01:14:54.244 --> 01:14:57.776
She squeezes the life
out of everybody.

01:14:57.778 --> 01:15:01.677
You've talked to
your mother about him?

01:15:01.679 --> 01:15:04.977
What's a man I've never known
got to do with all this?

01:15:07.078 --> 01:15:10.744
Have you ever had
irregular periods

01:15:10.746 --> 01:15:12.578
or excessive bleeding?

01:15:12.580 --> 01:15:14.444
You ask everyone that?

01:15:14.446 --> 01:15:16.545
Just the female
patients, of course.

01:15:16.547 --> 01:15:19.545
It's important to have a record

01:15:19.547 --> 01:15:22.512
of all your physical symptoms.

01:15:22.514 --> 01:15:28.546
All I know is that I'm...

01:15:28.548 --> 01:15:31.345
I'm feeling...

01:15:31.347 --> 01:15:34.612
is that I'm feeling...

01:15:34.614 --> 01:15:38.613
I... I feel...

01:15:38.615 --> 01:15:41.280
it...

01:15:41.282 --> 01:15:45.947
I f... It's...
I... It's...

01:15:45.949 --> 01:15:48.681
I... I feel...

01:15:48.683 --> 01:15:50.948
What do you feel, Lydia?

01:15:50.950 --> 01:15:52.714
Ill.

01:15:52.716 --> 01:15:55.282
No one wants the truth, do they?

01:15:55.284 --> 01:15:58.382
That does make me angry.
Write that down.

01:15:58.384 --> 01:16:00.115
I think there's
quite a lot going on

01:16:00.117 --> 01:16:03.248
under that anger.

01:16:03.250 --> 01:16:06.348
It's racing.

01:16:06.350 --> 01:16:08.715
It's like it's gonna jump out.

01:16:08.717 --> 01:16:12.583
I resent this idea that
we're just emotional.

01:16:12.585 --> 01:16:14.249
This is real.

01:16:14.251 --> 01:16:16.349
It's real in its
consequences, yes.

01:16:16.351 --> 01:16:19.050
What's important here is
that it's real to you.

01:16:19.052 --> 01:16:21.716
Real to me?
What does that mean?

01:16:21.718 --> 01:16:23.850
It's real to all of us.

01:16:23.852 --> 01:16:25.950
Something's seriously wrong.

01:16:25.952 --> 01:16:28.717
Why is everyone ignoring us?

01:16:42.120 --> 01:16:44.252
He's prescribed
tranquilizers for all of us.

01:16:44.254 --> 01:16:46.785
They don't seem to want
to believe we're ill.

01:16:46.787 --> 01:16:52.252
My advice...
don't take the pills

01:16:52.254 --> 01:16:54.220
and try to hide your symptoms.

01:16:54.222 --> 01:16:58.420
I'm finding, being in
the more advanced stages,

01:16:58.422 --> 01:17:00.187
that my symptoms don't
show as much, anyway.

01:17:00.189 --> 01:17:02.453
Advanced stages?

01:17:02.455 --> 01:17:05.754
Yeah, Connie,
being further along.

01:17:05.756 --> 01:17:07.453
I'm ahead.

01:17:07.455 --> 01:17:10.254
You just can't stand that
we're all feeling ill, too.

01:17:10.256 --> 01:17:13.254
No. I'm glad
you're ill.

01:17:13.256 --> 01:17:14.888
Well, no, not glad, but
you know what I mean.

01:17:14.890 --> 01:17:16.454
I'm gonna get my parents
to arrange for us

01:17:16.456 --> 01:17:18.122
to see a leading
medical specialist.

01:17:18.124 --> 01:17:19.521
Susan...
Susie.

01:17:19.523 --> 01:17:22.389
Come on!

01:17:22.391 --> 01:17:24.656
I'm not gonna let you down.

01:17:40.058 --> 01:17:42.356
Hysterical contagion...

01:17:42.358 --> 01:17:46.723
that's the diagnosis...
the wandering womb.

01:17:47.692 --> 01:17:49.257
Pardon?

01:17:49.259 --> 01:17:51.925
Hysteria, from the
Greek for uterus.

01:17:51.927 --> 01:17:53.858
Hippocrates believed
that the disordered womb

01:17:53.860 --> 01:17:56.891
led to hysteria.

01:17:59.092 --> 01:18:02.959
The standards of behavior
must be kept.

01:18:02.961 --> 01:18:04.859
This is a school.

01:18:04.861 --> 01:18:08.226
It's not a mental institution.

01:18:09.927 --> 01:18:12.293
This generation,

01:18:12.295 --> 01:18:15.259
they think they're
so misunderstood.

01:18:15.261 --> 01:18:16.760
If they'd any idea
what it's like

01:18:16.762 --> 01:18:18.093
to be a middle-aged woman,

01:18:18.095 --> 01:18:20.760
they'd know what
misunderstood meant.

01:18:28.395 --> 01:18:30.694
Oh...

01:18:38.696 --> 01:18:40.195
Ha!

01:18:58.764 --> 01:19:01.397
Sounds to me like they
didn't find anything wrong.

01:19:01.399 --> 01:19:04.064
The tests weren't
advanced enough.

01:19:07.299 --> 01:19:10.565
You didn't go mentioning me
to them, did you?

01:19:10.567 --> 01:19:11.765
The world doesn't revolve

01:19:11.767 --> 01:19:13.798
around you, Eileen.

01:19:13.800 --> 01:19:15.032
You know, I'm supposed to go see

01:19:15.034 --> 01:19:16.132
another psychiatrist.

01:19:16.134 --> 01:19:17.132
I don't think you'll have

01:19:17.134 --> 01:19:18.765
much choice but to come.

01:19:18.767 --> 01:19:20.199
They'll ask lots
of probing questions

01:19:20.201 --> 01:19:22.566
about you, you know.

01:19:22.568 --> 01:19:25.032
They're very interested
in exactly why

01:19:25.034 --> 01:19:27.799
I am like I am.

01:19:31.701 --> 01:19:33.400
Have you got any
idea what it's like

01:19:33.402 --> 01:19:35.466
having you as a mother?

01:19:35.468 --> 01:19:37.066
It's so unfair!

01:19:37.068 --> 01:19:38.433
Everything has to be
brought to you!

01:19:38.435 --> 01:19:39.900
What do you want with me?

01:19:41.769 --> 01:19:44.467
Well...

01:19:44.469 --> 01:19:47.668
what's Crazy Face
gone and done now?

01:20:07.404 --> 01:20:08.802
But, you know, I'm definitely

01:20:08.804 --> 01:20:10.436
in the advanced stages, too.

01:20:10.438 --> 01:20:11.869
That specialist
of yours will just

01:20:11.871 --> 01:20:14.303
put it down to female hormones.

01:20:14.305 --> 01:20:19.070
I mean, it could be
all kinds of things

01:20:19.072 --> 01:20:21.404
for all sorts of reasons.

01:20:27.139 --> 01:20:28.671
Tastes metallic.

01:20:32.738 --> 01:20:35.004
You're nothing
like her, you know.

01:20:37.573 --> 01:20:39.605
You've never actually
cried for Abbie,

01:20:39.607 --> 01:20:41.338
have you?

01:20:45.940 --> 01:20:50.539
Anyway, I've not
come to see you.

01:20:50.541 --> 01:20:53.307
Here to see Kenneth.

01:20:53.309 --> 01:20:55.307
Kenneth.

01:20:55.309 --> 01:20:58.640
We started seeing
each other now.

01:20:58.642 --> 01:21:00.907
You know, we've got
a real thing.

01:21:05.374 --> 01:21:07.807
I requested to see you, Lydia...

01:21:07.809 --> 01:21:10.641
You never liked her, did you?

01:21:10.643 --> 01:21:12.074
Excuse me?

01:21:12.076 --> 01:21:15.075
Her name's Abbie.

01:21:15.077 --> 01:21:16.474
As much as I'd like to take

01:21:16.476 --> 01:21:18.275
a close interest
in every pupil's...

01:21:18.277 --> 01:21:21.975
You gonna tell me
exactly what's going on?

01:21:21.977 --> 01:21:23.776
Are you?

01:21:27.910 --> 01:21:29.609
You're afraid of me.

01:21:30.945 --> 01:21:32.709
You're merely a girl.

01:21:35.744 --> 01:21:37.109
What you writing?

01:21:37.111 --> 01:21:39.910
It's nothing.
It's about me.

01:21:39.912 --> 01:21:43.110
You go around in that thing.

01:21:43.112 --> 01:21:46.744
You're so...
You're so...

01:21:46.746 --> 01:21:48.611
The school secretary
is personally visiting

01:21:48.613 --> 01:21:51.311
your mother this morning
to deliver the news.

01:21:51.313 --> 01:21:54.212
It is for the best, Lydia.

01:21:54.214 --> 01:21:56.778
It is with regret
that I must inform you...

01:21:56.780 --> 01:21:59.812
You can't.

01:21:59.814 --> 01:22:02.612
You can't get rid of me.
I have rights.

01:22:13.315 --> 01:22:15.546
So we thank you, Miss Charron,

01:22:15.548 --> 01:22:17.880
for your invaluable contribution
in recent years

01:22:17.882 --> 01:22:20.880
and give you good wishes
for the future,

01:22:20.882 --> 01:22:25.080
and finally in response
to recent events,

01:22:25.082 --> 01:22:28.148
I wish to clarify
that absolutely nothing

01:22:28.150 --> 01:22:32.648
has been found in any tests
on the school or on the pupils.

01:22:32.650 --> 01:22:35.981
We have a reassuringly clean
bill of health.

01:22:35.983 --> 01:22:39.381
Anyone that says otherwise
is willfully wrong.

01:22:51.951 --> 01:22:54.383
You'll never get rid of me.

01:22:54.385 --> 01:22:56.749
I will not tolerate
such conduct in this school.

01:22:56.751 --> 01:23:00.250
You all know something is wrong.

01:23:00.252 --> 01:23:02.217
Get her out.

01:23:02.219 --> 01:23:04.584
Are you not gonna
fight for the truth?

01:23:04.586 --> 01:23:05.951
What have you been reduced to...

01:23:05.953 --> 01:23:07.384
Prefects, get her out.

01:23:07.386 --> 01:23:08.884
inertia?

01:23:08.886 --> 01:23:10.284
You're all asleep.

01:23:10.286 --> 01:23:12.651
To be free, you must
be conscious.

01:23:12.653 --> 01:23:16.252
Kill the system!
It's killing you!

01:23:17.453 --> 01:23:19.885
Up, up up.

01:23:35.989 --> 01:23:37.987
It's gonna be the same thing

01:23:37.989 --> 01:23:40.087
every day
for the rest of our lives.

01:23:40.089 --> 01:23:43.787
Same thing every year
the rest of our lives.

01:23:53.456 --> 01:23:58.555
Lydia, you really should leave.

01:23:58.557 --> 01:24:01.322
To be free,
you must be conscious.

01:24:01.324 --> 01:24:04.455
Why does everyone want
to get rid of me?

01:24:04.457 --> 01:24:06.423
Uh! Uh!

01:24:10.891 --> 01:24:13.122
Get off of me.

01:24:17.757 --> 01:24:20.790
There's something here.

01:24:20.792 --> 01:24:22.224
I think they left something,

01:24:22.226 --> 01:24:23.324
some poison.

01:24:23.326 --> 01:24:26.058
You're wrong.

01:24:26.060 --> 01:24:29.124
Block the door.

01:24:34.492 --> 01:24:37.059
Stop it.

01:24:42.626 --> 01:24:44.259
What have I done to you?

01:24:44.261 --> 01:24:45.459
Done?

01:24:45.461 --> 01:24:47.092
You haven't done anything.

01:24:50.595 --> 01:24:53.227
They should've kept me
in the hospital.

01:24:53.229 --> 01:24:56.160
I'm mad. I'm crazy.

01:24:56.162 --> 01:24:58.827
You are not crazy, Lydia.

01:24:58.829 --> 01:25:00.260
You are not crazy.
You are not mad.

01:25:00.262 --> 01:25:03.261
We're normal.

01:25:03.263 --> 01:25:07.794
If it's real to me

01:25:07.796 --> 01:25:10.595
and made-up,

01:25:10.597 --> 01:25:12.461
I would've really been ill.

01:25:12.463 --> 01:25:15.595
What?
What about us?

01:25:15.597 --> 01:25:17.262
We've all had it, Lydia.

01:25:17.264 --> 01:25:18.728
I've not.

01:25:18.730 --> 01:25:21.596
We've all got it.
Nobody can just faint.

01:25:21.598 --> 01:25:22.995
I guess I started it.

01:25:22.997 --> 01:25:25.129
Well, it happened
to me very early,

01:25:25.131 --> 01:25:28.429
and, I can assure you,
I'm no faker.

01:25:28.431 --> 01:25:30.396
I'm not...
I'm not a copycat.

01:25:30.398 --> 01:25:33.296
All of the tests were negative,

01:25:33.298 --> 01:25:35.897
and how come the others
recovered so quickly?

01:25:35.899 --> 01:25:38.897
The psychiatrist said
if it was real to me...

01:25:42.432 --> 01:25:44.431
I don't think it is.

01:25:44.433 --> 01:25:45.764
You know what, Lydia?

01:25:50.599 --> 01:25:52.065
You're the fake.

01:26:01.666 --> 01:26:04.199
Everything's wrong.

01:26:14.969 --> 01:26:17.933
So...

01:26:17.935 --> 01:26:19.900
I'm expelled.

01:26:23.568 --> 01:26:26.235
Good for you.

01:26:28.502 --> 01:26:29.734
Teenagers.

01:26:38.270 --> 01:26:41.768
Feels like you're
blacking out, dying.

01:27:06.972 --> 01:27:09.971
Even you don't want me.

01:27:12.939 --> 01:27:15.805
It's not like that.

01:27:15.807 --> 01:27:17.405
You know it's not.

01:27:43.008 --> 01:27:44.808
Mm...

01:27:58.176 --> 01:27:59.775
Mm...

01:28:14.644 --> 01:28:17.776
Mm. Oh...

01:28:17.778 --> 01:28:20.143
Mm.
Mm.

01:28:20.145 --> 01:28:22.477
Ooh... oh...

01:29:12.949 --> 01:29:16.781
But it comes...

01:29:16.783 --> 01:29:19.816
small death.

01:29:23.251 --> 01:29:27.582
Hey, you, come on.
Come on.

01:29:27.584 --> 01:29:29.949
Get away from her!
Go on, you!

01:29:29.951 --> 01:29:31.817
Get the hell away!

01:29:31.819 --> 01:29:34.149
Get out of my house!
Get out!

01:29:34.151 --> 01:29:35.283
Stop it! You're...

01:29:35.285 --> 01:29:37.316
You get off me!

01:29:37.318 --> 01:29:40.683
Get. Go.
Get out of my house.

01:29:40.685 --> 01:29:43.184
Go on.

01:29:43.186 --> 01:29:45.784
Stop looking at her.
I mean it.

01:29:54.819 --> 01:29:57.418
You disgust me.

01:29:58.653 --> 01:30:01.919
You ought to be locked up.

01:30:01.921 --> 01:30:04.919
You're dangerous.

01:30:04.921 --> 01:30:06.986
I... I...

01:30:06.988 --> 01:30:08.786
I forgot he was...

01:30:08.788 --> 01:30:10.419
uh, my brother.

01:30:10.421 --> 01:30:14.020
You forgot?

01:30:14.022 --> 01:30:16.254
Oh, you've not been ill,

01:30:16.256 --> 01:30:17.820
but you are sick,

01:30:17.822 --> 01:30:19.387
and you're sick in the head.

01:30:38.956 --> 01:30:41.922
There's not a man to be trusted.

01:30:44.323 --> 01:30:47.522
I know he went and left you,

01:30:47.524 --> 01:30:50.823
but you must have
trusted him once,

01:30:50.825 --> 01:30:52.923
and you have two kids with him.

01:30:52.925 --> 01:30:54.257
One.
Two.

01:30:54.259 --> 01:30:55.857
There's me, remember?

01:30:55.859 --> 01:30:57.156
One.
Two.

01:30:57.158 --> 01:31:01.624
I can count.
Ha! What?

01:31:01.626 --> 01:31:03.824
You're not his.

01:31:06.626 --> 01:31:08.324
Huh.

01:31:10.093 --> 01:31:13.458
That's why he ran away.

01:31:15.326 --> 01:31:17.992
He's not mine?

01:31:17.994 --> 01:31:19.792
Just forget it.
It's history.

01:31:19.794 --> 01:31:22.192
It's my history.
Who is he?

01:31:22.194 --> 01:31:24.626
Is he... Is he
still alive?

01:31:24.628 --> 01:31:26.826
Oh, come on.
You've got to tell me.

01:31:26.828 --> 01:31:28.526
Well, was there...

01:31:28.528 --> 01:31:31.460
Is there something
wrong with him?

01:31:31.462 --> 01:31:34.326
There was, wasn't there?

01:31:36.527 --> 01:31:40.227
What's wrong with me?
Who am I?

01:31:51.595 --> 01:31:55.362
He came from the shadows...

01:31:55.364 --> 01:31:56.829
What?

01:31:58.329 --> 01:32:01.329
and then...

01:32:02.330 --> 01:32:04.129
he...

01:32:10.464 --> 01:32:14.397
Uh, uh, you mean...

01:32:16.331 --> 01:32:20.597
y... you were... you...

01:32:20.599 --> 01:32:26.597
you were... I... I'm...

01:32:26.599 --> 01:32:30.365
Ha! Oh...

01:32:30.367 --> 01:32:31.565
Ohh...

01:32:39.533 --> 01:32:44.132
And I look like him, don't I?

01:32:47.367 --> 01:32:53.833
Uh, I've grown up
looking like him.

01:32:55.969 --> 01:32:58.200
I... I always knew
something was wrong.

01:32:58.202 --> 01:33:02.734
Now I know. It was me.
It's always been me.

01:33:04.102 --> 01:33:06.101
I should never have said...

01:33:06.103 --> 01:33:08.768
I'm glad.
I know the truth.

01:33:44.038 --> 01:33:46.771
In time, this mantled oak,

01:33:46.773 --> 01:33:50.838
let's meet underneath it
the same day every year

01:33:50.840 --> 01:33:52.739
for the rest of our lives.

01:33:53.673 --> 01:33:57.572
In time, this mantled oak...

01:34:03.140 --> 01:34:05.506
Abbie!

01:34:07.540 --> 01:34:10.373
Abbie!

01:34:43.310 --> 01:34:46.643
Ha! Ha ha!

01:34:57.811 --> 01:35:00.510
Aah!

01:35:00.512 --> 01:35:03.144
Hmm...

01:35:03.146 --> 01:35:05.244
Abbie!

01:35:08.345 --> 01:35:10.411
Abbie!

01:35:15.779 --> 01:35:19.646
I feel so free!
Ha ha!

01:35:21.213 --> 01:35:24.046
Ha ha!
Lydia...

01:35:24.048 --> 01:35:26.313
Oh...

01:35:26.315 --> 01:35:28.946
Lydia, sweetie,
please come down.

01:35:28.948 --> 01:35:31.013
Ha ha ha!
Look at me, Mum.

01:35:31.015 --> 01:35:34.147
Look at me.
Watch me. Watch me.

01:35:34.149 --> 01:35:35.813
Watch me.
No, no, sweetie.

01:35:35.815 --> 01:35:37.214
Please, just come down.

01:35:37.216 --> 01:35:38.481
Abbie!

01:35:38.483 --> 01:35:40.648
Lydia, please come down.

01:35:40.650 --> 01:35:42.714
Ha ha ha!

01:35:42.716 --> 01:35:44.547
We could go to the seaside.

01:35:44.549 --> 01:35:46.881
Ha ha ha!
Ha ha ha!

01:35:46.883 --> 01:35:49.115
That'd be nice. We've
never been to the seaside.

01:35:53.383 --> 01:35:57.248
Uh...
I feel so real.

01:35:59.150 --> 01:36:05.516
I feel so awake,
free, so conscious.

01:36:05.518 --> 01:36:08.116
Ha! Ha ha!

01:36:08.118 --> 01:36:10.150
Lydi...

01:36:16.051 --> 01:36:18.183
Abbie!

01:36:26.352 --> 01:36:28.285
What the hell is the problem?

01:36:37.653 --> 01:36:39.452
My God.

01:36:39.454 --> 01:36:41.219
Uh...

01:36:44.221 --> 01:36:46.319
There's nothing wrong with you.

01:37:19.890 --> 01:37:24.223
"Our birth is but a sleep
and a forgetting:

01:37:24.225 --> 01:37:28.356
"The Soul that rises with us,
our life's Star,

01:37:28.358 --> 01:37:30.523
"Hath had elsewhere its setting,

01:37:30.525 --> 01:37:32.823
And cometh from afar."

01:37:48.327 --> 01:37:51.191
Ha ha!
Oh...

01:37:54.026 --> 01:37:55.358
Oh, thank God.

